title: Essene Bread
desc: This is a sprouted bread recipe - very old, and said to have been created back in the biblical days.  Also, this recipe literally, takes days to make. Your efforts and time will be well rewarded with a couple of the most singular breads-solid, sweet, and moist. Wheat berries are available from your local natural foods store.  Traditionally, Essene bread was probably baked on hot rocks under scorching sunlight, but where I and most of us live, this is not possible. Baking at the oven temperatures which I suggest might destroy the sprout enzymes, but monitoring baking loaves for much longer than 2 hours is too long for me. Guaranteeing the preservation of the enzymes might require baking at a very low temperature for perhaps 4 hours. If you have the stamina, then go for it.

desc: An easy to make batter bread it's also called Sally Lunn Bread.

title: Blueberry Orange Bread
desc: This a very simple recipe to make and a very flavorful one at that, I do believe that everyone will love it! You may use thawed frozen blueberries if fresh ones are unavailable.

title: Pan Dulce
desc: These Mexican sweet buns have a streusel topping. A chocolate streusel variation is included.  You can shape these into seashells, ovals, or horns.

title: Honey and Flaxseed Bread
desc: A delicious whole grain bread.  It is my favorite bread of all time!  It is for bread makers. You may substitute vegetable oil for flaxseed oil if flaxseed oil is unavailable.

title: Creamy Banana Bread
desc: I have been using this recipe for a few years now, and it remains my family's favorite for banana bread! The combination of bananas and cream cheese make this a very moist bread.

title: Whole Wheat Banana Nut Bread
desc: This is a moist banana bread recipe that I make fairly often with leftover, very ripe bananas.

title: San Francisco Sourdough Bread
desc: Use a good sourdough starter, one you have tended to, for best flavor.

title: Fougasse
desc: This recipe for fougasse, the French version of the Italian focaccia bread, is topped with mixed herbs.  The flat bread can be slashed to form shapes (a leaf, tree, or wheat stalk), or the slits can be cut to form a lattice, making the bread easy to pull apart.

title: Strawnana Bread
desc: Quick and easy to make, oh so fruity, and very yummy!!

title: Morning Glory Muffins I
desc: This muffin has a little bit of everything - carrots, raisins, apple butter, wheat germ, nuts. A perfect start for your day!

title: Herman Sourdough Starter
desc: This is a recipe for a sweet sourdough starter known as Herman. There are a number of things that can be made from it. It's very important to NOT use metal utensils or bowls! It will take 15 days for the starter to mature and be ready to use the first time you make it. After that it can be ready for use every 10 days.

title: Herman Biscuits
desc: This is a great biscuit recipe for using Herman sourdough starter.

title: Herman Coffee Cake
desc: This cake like bread is the perfect accompaniment to your morning cup of coffee. It uses Herman sweet sourdough starter.

title: Favorite Banana Blueberry Quick Bread
desc: This is so good and reminds me of a real moist kind of a sweet quick bread.  Everybody asks for the recipe: this bread is moist, and easy to make too.  Note: If you are using frozen blueberries, you can thaw them in the microwave for about 3 minutes.  However, you need to increase the amount of blueberries to 3/4 cup.

title: Honey Bran Muffins
desc: These muffins are made with bran cereal, and sweetened with pineapple juice, brown sugar, and honey.  The recipe requires the batter to be refrigerated for at least 3 hours.  It can be made the night before, and then baked in the morning.  Makes 20 regular muffins, or 12 jumbo muffins.

title: Welsh Bread
desc: A slightly sweet bread with a great flavor combination of raisins and caraway seeds.

title: Cherry Vanilla Chip Muffins
desc: These are wheat free, dairy free, low sugar, low fat muffins and you'd never know it. Sucant is dried can juice. It can be found in health food stores. If you don't eat them in the first two days, freeze them. Thaw in microwave for 30 seconds apiece and they will taste freshly baked.

title: Chocolate Zucchini Muffins
desc: A wonderful way to use the extra bounty of summer, and make a tasty treat. You can adjust the recipe to suit your family's tastes, or create your own variations. For an optional topping use any, all or a combination of the following: equal parts  brown sugar, chopped nuts and mini chocolate chips. Sprinkle tops of muffins just prior to baking.

title: Herman Cinnamon Rolls
desc: Another recipe for the Herman Sweet Sourdough Starter in case you're having trouble giving it away! Try finishing these rolls with your favorite glaze!

title: Herman Dinner Rolls
desc: Yet another use for your Herman starter. For a variation try making a loaf of bread from your dough. Bake at 325 degrees F (165 degrees C) for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: Six Week Bran Muffins
desc: This batter can be stored in your refrigerator, unbaked for 6 weeks. Use only the amount you want each day. Mine never seems to last that long!

title: Schlotsky's Bread
desc: The dough will look resemble a batter, almost pourable. Take care not to add too much flour. If using all-purpose flour, use a little less as it is heavier than bread flour. Great to eat hot from the oven with butter.

title: Navajo Fry Bread I
desc: A traditional Native American bread. Great served with honey, jam, or butter.

title: Banana Chai Bread
desc: A low-fat banana bread flavored with chai. Chai is a spicy Indian tea, which should be available in many supermarkets.

title: Soft, Moist and Gooey Cinnamon Buns
desc: I tried long and hard to find the ultimate cinnamon bun recipe for bread machines...this is it. They are so soft and yummy!

title: Bread Pudding II
desc: My family LOVES bread pudding, and this recipe is one that I have fine tuned to their taste. I have to double this recipe, and bake it in a 9x13 inch pan for my family!  It's great for breakfast or dessert and is delicious with milk poured on top! Enjoy!

title: Bread Machine Bagels
desc: Quick and easy bagels you can make with your bread machine! You can use whatever topping that you wish, many like poppy seeds.

title: Beignets
desc: A traditional New Orleans-style recipe for their famous beignets! Grab a cafe au lait and you're set!

title: Sourdough Pancakes
desc: Yet another way to utilize your sourdough starter. Try topping these yummy pancakes with fresh fruit and whipped cream. I hope you like them! The amount of water can be adjusted depending on the consistency of your starter.

title: Jelly Doughnuts
desc: You can use any flavor of jelly or jam to make this recipe. Serve plain, sugared, or frosted.

title: Old-Fashioned Sally Lunn Muffins
desc: This is an old Southern recipe for a quick and easy solution to a need for homemade muffins.

title: Norwegian Flat Bread
desc: This is a wonderful whole wheat cracker-like bread. It is great topped with butter or cheese. Better yet, it is simple, too!

title: Easy Biscuit Mixture
desc: Use as you would a baking mix. The possibilities are endless!

title: Gluten-Free White Bread for Bread Machines
desc: A basic white bread recipe without the gluten. Easily made in your bread machine! Xanthan gum and the exotic flours are usually easily found in your local health food store.

title: Coconut Muffins
desc: A very simple muffin recipe. Try them with your favorite hot beverage for an early morning treat. Quick note: if using sweetened coconut, eliminate the honey.

title: Zucchini Pineapple Bread II
desc: This is a quick bread that my mom used to make every summer with the zucchinis from the garden.

title: Pizza Crust for Bread Machine
desc: A crusty, chewy pizza crust!  Our family's favorite! Try make two pizza crusts at once by removing the dough from the machine once it hits the rise cycle and place in a separate bowl. Now you are ready to begin the second crust!

title: Spinach Bread
desc: Hearty and delicious, this bread tastes and smells great.

title: Jo Jo's Favorite Banana Muffins
desc: This is my favorite recipe. I have had this recipe since I was in high school. All my friends love it. Hope you enjoy it!

title: Real Southern Cornbread
desc: This is the real stuff!  Find your cast iron skillet and whip up a batch of cornbread tonight!

title: Herb Biscuits
desc: This is a great recipe for showers, luncheons, or other parties. It can be easily doubled or tripled.

title: Cheese Biscuits II
desc: A tasty biscuit with a flavor kick courtesy of bell pepper and pimentos.

title: Zucchini Bread V
desc: A moist bread with different spices than standard zucchini bread recipes. This is the best one I've tried, thanks to my stepmom-in-law. I like to freeze the shredded zucchini, and make this in the fall and winter. It's wonderful to serve at the Thanksgiving table.

title: Prosciutto Filling for Calzones
desc: Another way to fill your calzones!

title: Banana Nut and Ginger Bread
desc: Dark beer adds a unique twist to this recipe. You may substitute raisins or currants for the dates if you wish.

title: Lemon Poppy Seed Amish Friendship Bread
desc: This is a yummy variation of Amish Friendship Bread.  It's one of my family's favorites! It's versatile enough to make muffins, too. Just add 3 tablespoons of the batter into greased muffin tins and reduce the baking time to 23-25 minutes.

title: Crunchy Honey Wheat Bread
desc: The Moss Family's favorite bread. Great flavor and easy to make!

title: Paximade
desc: This bread is a greek type of bread that tastes almost like cake, although the sugar content is much lower. It makes a terrific breakfast bread.

title: Cuban Water Bread
desc: This recipe is from my mom. Makes a very crusty bread. You can substitute half of the flour amount with whole wheat flour.

title: Southern Biscuits with Mayonnaise
desc: A tender, old-fashioned Southern biscuit recipe from my mother-in-law. Grab your cast iron skillet, and you are ready to make these tasty biscuits!

title: Granny's Oatmeal Bread
desc: Granny's best bread recipe, ever! Try it for yourself!

title: Nana's Fastnachts
desc: These are similar to doughnuts but much tastier! They are usually made on Shrove Tuesday (Fat Tuesday).

title: Kalamata Olive and Garlic Bread
desc: This bread was created from leftover dough after making a foccacia dressed with Kalamata olives, garlic, and olive oil. This version has the olives and garlic baked in the bread.

title: Cheese Herb Bread
desc: Fantastic with any Italian dish! I use fresh herbs from my garden when they are available. When using fresh herbs, double the given amount. The smell will make it impossible to wait. ENJOY!

title: Deluxe Waffles
desc: This is a soft waffle. A childhood favorite.

title: Pear Bread I
desc: This bread is great lightly toasted for breakfast or anytime!

title: Pumpkin Yeast Bread
desc: This bread is so good and it makes the house smell heavenly while it bakes!

title: Sweet Corn Cake
desc: A Mexican sweet corn cake with a spoon bread consistency.

title: Pepperoni Pizza Bread
desc: This is a great treat! Very different from the usual bread-machine breads!  It is perfect served fresh and warm or toasted and then broiled with a little mozzarella cheese. Enjoy!

title: Rye Starter
desc: This is a traditional sourdough rye starter made with wild yeast.  It takes some time, and a watchful eye.

title: Wild Grape Starter
desc: Use unwashed, organically grown red or purple grapes for this recipe. The white powder found on the skins of the grapes is yeast.   If you wish, you can switch to bread flour on the 5th day.  The starter is fully active and ready to use in 9 days.

title: Muesli-Applesauce Muffins
desc: They are juicy and crunchy. Try them and you'll enjoy them! Muesli cereal is  blend of cereal grains and can sometimes include dried fruits.

title: Double Quick Dinner Rolls
desc: An easy, delicious dinner roll to prepare--no shaping needed. You may want to double the recipe!

title: Banana Chocolate Chip Muffins
desc: Banana and chocolate, a great combination, they go so well together! Quick and easy to make as well.

title: Pan de Muertos (Mexican Bread of the Dead)
desc: This is a version of the bread that is made for the November 2 celebration known as the Dia de los Muertos (Day of the Dead) in Mexico. You can also mold the bread into different shapes like angels and animals.

title: Cracked Wheat Sourdough Bread
desc: A hearty grain and seed filled sourdough bread. Any good sourdough starter will work in this bread. The Rye Starter is just an example of one type of starter to use.

title: Sourdough Buckwheat Pancakes
desc: Buckwheat pancakes are the best! I love them with a fresh blueberry syrup and loads of sweet cream butter!

title: Chocolate Chip Sourdough Muffins
desc: Yummy muffins made with a sourdough starter, just the way my grandmother (a professional baker) taught me.

title: Delightful Apple Spice Muffins
desc: These moist muffins are really small, that's what makes them cute! The spiciness makes them delightfully delicious!

title: Skiers' French Toast
desc: A baked French toast that makes it's own syrup. You prepare it the night before then bake it in the morning. Great for a crowd at breakfast like a sleepover party or before heading up to the slopes!

title: Pumpkin Chip Bread
desc: Glazed pumpkin bread with chocolate chips. This is really good stuff.

title: Granny's Corn Flour Tortillas
desc: Granny made these and every time I make them I think of her. Hope you enjoy them! Serve these with your favorite burrito or fajita recipe!

title: Corn Yeast Rolls
desc: These are my favorite rolls in the whole world. They have the corny taste of a cornmeal muffin, but are a yeast roll that you can serve with a fancy dinner.

title: Grandma Emma's Spice Loaf
desc: A quick bread, moist and full of raisins and nuts. A family favorite for the winter holidays.

title: Portuguese Sweet Bread II
desc: This sweet Portuguese bread  is made in the bread machine.

title: Challah in a Hurry
desc: Made with quick-rise yeast, this is a sweeter, richer challah that lends itself especially well to Rosh Hashanah or other holiday uses. It is  quicker and easier than a standard double-rise recipe, so it's great for those afternoons when you're in a challah of a hurry. Challah was meant to be torn and not sliced. B'tayevon!

title: Jam Muffins
desc: These fruity muffins make a perfect snack or light breakfast, plus they're easy to make!

title: Popovers
desc: A light and airy favorite bread treat. Serve piping hot and enjoy!

title: Rum Raisin Bread
desc: This bread is a little sweeter and richer than the usual raisin bread.  For best results, soak the raisins in rum overnight and measure the raisins after soaking.

title: Pseudo Sourdough for the Bread Machine
desc: This is white bread with a delicious taste twist. Note: Use only real sour cream for this recipe! But if you don't have barley flour on hand you may substitute bread flour.

title: Apple Cheddar Bread
desc: This recipe was given to me a while back and it is great on Sunday  mornings.  My boys just love it!

title: Cardamom Banana Bread
desc: This fragrant bread is better than original banana bread. If you don't have cardamom, you can substitute ground nutmeg. This bread keeps for 5 days without refrigeration.

title: Pumpkin Pie Bread
desc: This quick bread recipe tastes like pumpkin pie. Tastes best when served the next day.

title: Southern Sweet Potato Bread with Pecans
desc: A fragrant southern style quick bread. Perfect for the holidays.

title: Jay's Signature Pizza Crust
desc: This recipe yields a crust that is soft and doughy on the inside and slightly crusty on the outside. Cover it with your favorite sauce and topping to make a delicious pizza.

title: Aunt Bert's White Cake
desc: This is a very old recipe that I got from my deceased friend Holli's Aunt Bert.  Everyone will love it.

title: Easy Plain Cake
desc: The EASIEST way of making the original flavor of Cakes!

title: Peanut Butter Cake I
desc: Get nostalgic with this recipe for peanut butter cake featuring a simple frosting.

title: Sourdough Chocolate Cranberry Cake
desc: A prize winning chocolate cranberry cake made with a sourdough starter.

title: Donna's Pound Cake
desc: A delicious, moist and easy cake that tastes like you spent lots of time making it!!

title: Chocolate Zucchini Cake I
desc: This cake can be frozen for up to 6 months. To make sour milk, mix 1/2 cup milk with 2 teaspoons lemon juice and let stand 10 minutes.

title: Mocha Blanca Cheesecake
desc: This recipe is for the serious cheesecake lover. It is very rich and definitely not low fat. It is best to prepare for dinner guests where a little slice will go a long way. I prefer to make it without the topping, but it is just as good with it. The longer you are able to refrigerate it before serving the better it gets.  Enjoy!

title: Carrot Cake II
desc: This recipe delivers a low-fat version of a perennial favorite through use of applesauce: carrot cake with walnuts, raisins, and pineapple.

title: Dirt Cake I
desc: This is a great conversation piece at parties.  Adults love it as much as the children do.  Get a new garden trowel, medium sized flower pot and artificial flower at a craft store for full effect.

title: Chocolate Chip Oatmeal Cake
desc: This quick and simple recipe makes enough chocolate chip-studded cake to delight a crowd.

title: Pol's Apple Cake
desc: This is a rich apple cake served with a warm topping that my grandmother used to make for me.  Delicious! This recipe calls for walnuts but pecans are just as delicious!

title: Grandma's Eggless, Butterless, Milkless Cake
desc: You can get a moist chocolate cake without eggs, butter, or milk thanks to this recipe, tested by Grandma and approved by all who try it.

title: Italian Cream Cake I
desc: This is a wonderful, award winning cake. Feel free to substitute your favorite nuts for the walnuts.

title: Texas Sheet Cake I
desc: This is an easy and very good potluck cake.  Serves several.

title: Streusel Coffee Cake
desc: This is great for brunches or family get-togethers, or just any ol' time. It is really good when still warm. I make this cake for Christmas and Easter breakfast when family and friends are here.

title: Boiled Raisin Cake I
desc: This cake doesn't need frosting or icing. It is easy for kids to make, and is hard to mess up.

title: Waldorf Astoria Red Cake
desc: My mom used to make this when I was little. It is a very rich and elegant cake. The frosting is very unusual tasting in that it is almost like a custard.

title: Krazy Kake
desc: This cake is great for potlucks. It is easy to make, and is mixed and baked in the same pan. We got this recipe back in the Girl Scout days, and it has always been a hit!

title: Cocoa Apple Cake
desc: This recipe is very moist and rich. I have also made it in loaf pans, and given it away for holidays.

title: Best Cheesecake on Earth
desc: A great cheesecake made with ricotta cheese AND cream cheese!

title: Grandma Snyder's Oatmeal Cake
desc: This is a great cake for any sweet tooth.  It is good served hot too.

title: Fabulous Fudge Chocolate Cake
desc: This is my favorite chocolate cake recipe because of the moist texture and rich, dark chocolate flavor.  Enjoy!

title: No Bake Cheesecake I
desc: This is as quick and easy as cheesecake recipes get, using cookies and graham crackers for a crust in a no-bake cheesecake.

title: Pumpkin Pie Cake I
desc: This is a good winter holiday cake. Great when topped with whipped cream or nondairy whipped topping.

title: Awesome Carrot Cake with Cream Cheese Frosting
desc: This straightforward recipe delivers moist, dense, and delicious carrot cake with pineapple under a cream cheese frosting.

title: Chantilly Cake Frosting
desc: This cake is a Hawaiian favorite. Make your favorite chocolate cake.  The real secret is in the frosting.

title: Plum Bread
desc: This is called a bread, but tastes more like a cake. I make this mostly during the holidays. The spices in this cake just lend themselves to eggnog and Christmas smells. The recipe will make 1 bundt cake, 4 small loaves, or 2 medium loaves.

title: Mom's Carrot Cake
desc: The difference between this and other carrot cakes is the fact that the carrots  are pre-cooked instead of raw. It is a really moist cake that is better the day after it is made. Cake tastes best after refrigerating overnight.

title: Easy Lemon Cake
desc: I got this recipe from my mother-in-law years ago, and it has always been a family favorite. It is real good for potlucks as it is served right out of the pan.

title: French Buttercream Frosting
desc: This buttercream is great for icing cakes, and writing on them.  It gets hard when refrigerated, so you have to let it come to room temperature before serving.  You cannot make flowers with this recipe.  I use this recipe every time I make birthday cakes for my family.

title: Brownie Torte
desc: This torte is delicious and very rich with a brownie-like texture studded with walnuts and topped with a chocolate glaze.

title: Pecan Sour Cream Pound Cake
desc: I won first place with this cake at the Cuyahoga County Fair (Cleveland, Ohio) in 1993. For a nuttier variation, you can substitute 1 cup of the flour with 1 cup of ground pecans.

title: Chocolate Cherry Cake I
desc: This recipe uses chocolate cake mix and cherry pie filling for an easy and delicious cake with a frosting made with chocolate chips.

title: Pecan Pound Cake
desc: This easy recipe makes a wonderfully moist pound cake with plenty of butter and pecans.

title: Easy Streusel Coffee Cake
desc: Yellow cake mix with nutty, chocolate, cinnamon streusel.

title: Irish Cream Chocolate Cheesecake
desc: If you like Irish cream and chocolate, you'll love this recipe. After numerous attempts with the ingredients this is the recipe I now use.

title: Microwave Cake
desc: Easy fast cake that can be made in the microwave in approximately 12 minutes.  My favorite combinations are:  chocolate cake mix with cherry pie filling or yellow cake mix with apple pie filling ( I add a bit of cinnamon for flavor to this one.)

title: Creme de Menthe Cake I
desc: This quick recipe uses regular cake mix, any brand, and any type of whipped topping.   It is a great dessert for after dinner, or anytime and especially a treat for St. Patrick's Day (easy way to get something "green").  You can use creme de menthe flavoring if you don't have the actual liqueur.

title: Lick Your Lips Cake
desc: Fruity, creamy cake that keeps them coming back for "just one more little piece"!

title: Dump Cake I
desc: This cake is just as easy as dumping ingredients in a pan.

title: Texas Sheet Cake II
desc: Rich, moist, easy chocolate cake to feed a crowd. Small serving is more than enough. Great for community dinners or large get togethers of any sort.

title: Miss Beth's Yoghurt Cake
desc: This is a light, tasty cake that's perfect for dessert or breakfast!  It's easy to make and will become one of your favorites!

title: Cherry Nut Cake I
desc: This recipe uses cherry pie filling to make a quick and good dump cake with walnuts.

title: Quick Fudge Icing
desc: This recipe requires just a few ingredients to make an easy, quick, and good chocolate icing for cakes, brownies, or cookies.

title: Chocolate Cherry Upside Down Cake
desc: This is an old favorite from my recipe box that I have had for 25 years that 's  non-dairy and egg free!

title: Chocolate Pound Cake I
desc: This was my mother's recipe.  You may eat it as is or put a fudge frosting on it.

title: Quick Black Forest Cake
desc: This version of Black Forest cake gets you an easy, delicious, and moist cake by using cherry pie filling and devil's food cake mix.

title: Carrot Cake I
desc: This recipe makes a sumptuous carrot cake with cinnamon accents and a homemade cream cheese glaze.

title: Key Lime Cake I
desc: Key limes give flavor and a tangy twist to this delicious, buttery glazed-cake recipe.

title: Pineapple Cake I
desc: Finally ... here is an easy, delicious, cake for pineapple lovers!  And it's lower in fat than most other cakes!

title: Botercake (Butter Cake)
desc: This is a Dutch recipe for 'buttercake' made with plenty of butter, of course, and lemon and vanilla for flavor.

title: The Best Chocolate Cake You Ever Ate
desc: I make this cake over and over.  It is easy to put together and the frosting of the cake is easy and fast.  It goes fast around my house.

title: Butter Pound Cake
desc: This is a real rich pound cake which is tasty alone or with ice cream or a fruit topping such as peaches.

title: Eclair Cake
desc: This is a very quick and simple no bake dessert cake. It uses graham crackers and a pudding mixture. It tastes just like an eclair, but there is enough for a crowd!! It is a great recipe for children who are learning to cook, there is no baking involved or any power kitchen tools. Just a bowl and a spoon!

title: Banana Cake I
desc: This old-fashioned banana cake recipe uses buttermilk for extra complexity in flavor.

title: Surprise Banana Cake
desc: This is an old Seattle recipe for a simple cake to turn overripe bananas into a delicious dessert.

title: Mini Cheesecakes I
desc: Easy and so good for holidays, weddings, or whatever the occasion!  It is also good with other flavors of fruit pie filling.

title: Apricot Sponge Cake
desc: Enticingly good served with fresh-off-the-tree apricots. Garnish cake with fresh sliced apricots and dollops of whipped cream or creme fraiche sprinkle with confectioners' sugar if desired.

title: Chocolate Cake I
desc: This is a simple recipe but it makes a rich chocolate cake thanks to the addition of grated chocolate and sour cream.

title: Favorite Chocolate Cake
desc: This is always a hit!  I use a mint flavored frosting for this cake.

title: Orange Sponge Cake
desc: Why not try this citrus cake on a very hot summer day?

title: Philadelphia Red Cake
desc: Using lemon juice to sour milk in this recipe helps make this chocolate cake very moist and flavorful.

title: Great Chocolate Cake
desc: It's a very rich fudgy chocolate cake, and is so easy to make!

title: Quick Sunshine Cake
desc: This recipe was given to me by a friend with whom I exchange recipes.  It is so moist and good.  Being a nurse,  I am always looking for quick easy recipes.

title: Double Chocolate Cake I
desc: This is a very good chocolate cake, when frosted with a chocolate frosting it is a double chocolate treat.

title: Coconut Pound Cake
desc: My grandchildren love this recipe for a coconut-flavored pound cake.

title: Pineapple Layer Cake
desc: This is a plain white layer cake with a creamy pineapple filling.

title: Favorite Old Fashioned Gingerbread
desc: This is everyone's holiday favorite, even the busy cook's, because it is so easy to make.

title: Glorious Sponge Cake
desc: This is an old fashioned sponge cake with a lemon flavor.

title: Angel Food Cake I
desc: Homemade angel food cake is worth the work.  It is moist, unlike the sweet styrofoam available in the grocery bakery.  A tube pan with a removable bottom is highly recommended.

title: Sour Cream Chocolate Cake
desc: This is a rich chocolate cake with a fudge frosting.  If you don't have sour cream, you can use sweet cream and add 1 tablespoon of lemon juice or vinegar.

title: Cream Cheese Pound Cake I
desc: My children always loved this cake.  They are grown now, but when they come home they ask me to have "the cake" made.  It is an easy recipe.

title: Earthquake Cake I
desc: This is like eating an upside down german chocolate cake.

title: Worm Cake
desc: A favorite of youngsters in our house. Grownups love them too!

title: Karen A's Chocolate Dump Cake
desc: This rich chocolate cake is very easy to make.

title: Maraschino Cherry Nut Cake
desc: A very good and moist cake with a lovely pink color perfect for birthdays, showers, or anniversaries.

title: Buttercream Cake Frosting
desc: A touch of red food coloring gives this buttercream frosting recipe a lovely pink hue.

title: Green Cake
desc: This cake isn't really green, it's the frosting that's green and unique.

title: Strawberry Cake I
desc: Use white cake mix and strawberry gelatin mix to make this recipe for the best strawberry cake ever!

title: Ricotta Cheese Cake
desc: It's a wonderful, easy, light cheese filled cake... but not a cheesecake!

title: Fruit Cocktail Cake I
desc: A lovely fruit cocktail cake, simple and delicious.

title: Pistachio Cake I
desc: This is a very good tasting cake, and easy to make.

title: Passover Brownie Cake
desc: I experimented for years to come up with a brownie made with matzoh... this is the best!

title: Banana Nut Coconut Cake
desc: The melding of banana, coconut and pecans give this cake a unique flavor. Best if made a day before serving.

title: Cinnamon Teacake
desc: Quick and easy cake topped with cinnamon sugar. Quite good for breakfast.

title: Easy Raisin Cake
desc: A not too sweet cake packed with raisins.  Perfect with coffee or tea and a wonderful departure from the typically sweet holiday goodies.

title: Cassata alla Siciliana (Sicilian Cream Tart)
desc: A beautiful sponge layer cake filled with a delightful ricotta cheese filling.

title: Banana Nut Frosting
desc: Yummy banana-coconut frosting.

title: Gingerbread I
desc: Gingerbread is an old-fashioned, warm, and spicy treat you can make easily at home with this recipe.

title: Coconut Cake I
desc: This cake starts with a white cake mix and ends up with four layers with a yummy coconut filling.

title: Fresh Pineapple Upside Down Cake
desc: The classic pineapple upside down cake made with fresh pineapple. Serve with dollops of creme fraiche.

title: Creamy White Layers
desc: A luscious, tender cake that goes well with many different types of fillings and frostings.

title: Devil's Food Cake I
desc: This is an old-fashioned, but easy-to-make devil's food cake recipe.  Pound cake like texture and sinfully chocolately.  This is from an old Philadelphia Bakery. Great when frosted with Chocolate Fudge Buttercream Frosting.

title: Chocolate Fudge Buttercream Frosting
desc: Easy and creamy chocolate fudge frosting. Tastes heavenly. Use on cooled devil's food cake for a death by chocolate experience.

title: Auntie's Buttermilk Cake
desc: I got this recipe, as well as so many others, from my favorite aunt.    She loved to bake--she used to say it was her "therapy," and I feel the same way!

title: Our Favorite Chocolate Cake
desc: This is the cake my family always traditionally took on picnics and any other family get-together. Cream may be substituted for the milk for a richer cake.

title: Coffee Frosting
desc: Delicious coffee flavored chocolate frosting. Cream may be substituted for the milk for added richness.

title: Norwegian Hazelnut Cake
desc: This cake has a sweet, rich flavor, and is easy to make.

title: Vasilopita
desc: This is our family's New Year's cake.  A coin is baked in the cake, and the person who finds the coin in their slice is has good luck for the year; they also get a prize.

title: Chocolate Mint Cheesecake
desc: This cheesecake is made with bittersweet chocolate. Beautiful garnished with fresh mint leaves.

title: Melt In Your Mouth Blueberry Cake
desc: This is a nice tender cake - one of my Mom's specialties from years ago.  It is a great cake to take along to a picnic.

title: Fabulous Oatmeal-Bran Cake

desc: Get ready to do the hula!  Good with cream cheese or sour cream frosting.

title: Japanese Fruit Cake I

title: Black Forest Cake I

title: Chocolate Rapture Cake

title: Cooky Corn Cake
desc: Cream corn in a sweet cake! Why not?

title: Wacky Cake V

desc: Start with yellow cake mix and Mandarin oranges to make this cake with a frosting made with pineapple, pudding mixture, and whipped topping.

title: Sock It to Me Cake IV

title: Fudgy Cream Cheese Tunnel Cake
desc: A dense tunnel of chocolaty cream cheese winds through this cake, which is so decadent, yet surprisingly easy.

title: Easy Rich Chocolate Cake
desc: This is a very easy-to-make chocolate cake. Also very rich!  It's sure to please.

title: Orange Oatmeal Muffins
desc: These are moist muffins with a hint of orange flavoring in it. I received this recipe from my great aunt at the time I was married.

title: Sweet Potato Cake
desc: A spicy layer cake. Good with buttercream frosting.

title: Shoo Fly Cake
desc: A variation on the old Pennsylvania Dutch favorite, Shoo Fly Pie. Not as sweet or gooey as Shoo Fly Pie, this cake is much better the day after you bake it. Works really well as cupcakes.  I made mini cupcakes for Christmas, always a hit.

title: Hardly Hard Sauce
desc: A wonderful recipe for kids and adults

title: Cameo Cake

title: Maple Icing

title: Japanese Fruit Cake II

title: Chocolate Mayonnaise Cake II
desc: Mayonnaise and cocoa powder are two of the eight ingredients in this quick and easy recipe for a moist cake.

title: Oat Bran Muffins

title: Texas Sheet Cake III

title: Cranberry Cake

title: Easy Chocolate Banana Cake

title: Pralines, Coffee and Cream Cake

title: Coconut Frosting and Filling

title: Pumpkin Roll Cake

title: New Duchess Spice Cake with Maple Buttercream Frosting

title: Best Buttercream Frosting

desc: Very moist and rich. A favorite of my two grown sons. It keeps very well.

title: Good For You Cheesecake

title: Banana Cake V

title: Funnel Cakes IV

title: Bible Cake
